The paper deals with pattern mining, which is a subfield of data mining and machine learning. The focus is on negative sequential patterns, which are commonly used in databases and data mining. Therefore, cs.DB (Databases) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves formal study and algorithm development, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also discusses support, which is a common measure in data mining, and proposes dominance and equivalence relations, which are concepts in mathematics, indicating that it could also belong to cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). Finally, the paper involves statistical analysis, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning).
